name: BENE_SK
comment: A UNIQUE NUMBER ASSIGNED BY THE ENROLLMENT DATA BASE (EDB) TO EACH EDB RECORD TO IDENTIFY A BENEFICIARY.

name: IDR_TRANS_EFCTV_TS
comment: THE SYSTEM DATE AND TIME ASSIGNED BY THE INTEGRATED DATA REPOSITORY (IDR) IDENTIFYING WHEN A RECORD IS LOADED.

name: IDR_TRANS_OBSLT_TS
comment: THE SYSTEM DATE AND TIME ASSIGNED BY THE INTEGRATED DATA REPOSITORY (IDR) WHEN A RECORD WAS LAST KNOWN TO BE PRESENT IN THE SOURCE. THE CURRENT VERSION OF A RECORD WILL BE SET TO 12/31/9999 00:00:00.

name: BENE_XREF_EFCTV_SK
comment: AN INTEGRATED DATA REPOSITORY (IDR) DERIVED EFFECTIVE SURROGATE KEY THAT UNIQUELY IDENTIFIES A BENEFICIARY.  NOTE: BENE_XREF_EFCTV_SK REPRESENTS THE MOST CURRENT BENE_SK THAT IS IN EFFECT FOR THE BENEFICIARY. BENE_XREF_EFCTV_SK IS MORE CURRENT THAN BENE_SK AND BENE_XREF_SK ON THE BENE TABLE.

name: BENE_BIC_CD
comment: A CODE IDENTIFYING A BENEFICIARYS RELATIONSHIP TO A PRIMARY SOCIAL SECURITY ADMINISTRATION (SSA) OR RAILROAD RETIREMENT BOARD (RRB) WAGE EARNER AND USED TO JUSTIFY ENTITLEMENT TO MEDICARE BENEFITS. THE BENEFICIARY IDENTIFICATION CODE (BIC) IS USED IN CONJUNCTION WITH THE BENEFICIARYS CLAIM ACCOUNT NUMBER (CAN) TO UNIQUELY IDENTIFY A MEDICARE BENEFICIARY AND FORM A HEALTH INSURANCE CLAIM NUMBER (HICN).    REFERENCE TABLE: BENE_BIC_CD

name: BENE_BRTH_DT
comment: A DATE IDENTIFYING WHEN A BENEFICIARY IS BORN.

name: BENE_CAN_NUM
comment: A NUMBER IDENTIFYING THE PRIMARY BENEFICIARY UNDER THE SOCIAL SECURITY ADMINISTRATION (SSA) OR RAILROAD RETIREMENT BOARD (RRB) PROGRAM. THIS CLAIM ACCOUNT NUMBER(CAN), ALONG WITH THE BENEFICIARY IDENTIFICATION CODE, UNIQUELY IDENTIFIES A MEDICARE BENEFICIARY.

name: BENE_DEATH_DT
comment: A DATE IDENTIFYING WHEN A BENEFICIARY DIED.

name: BENE_DOD_PROOF_CD
comment: A CODE IDENTIFYING THE SOURCE THAT PROVIDED THE DATE OF DEATH INFORMATION.

name: BENE_ELGBL_REC_TYPE_CD
comment: A CODE IDENTIFYING IF THE ELIGIBILITY INFORMATION REFERS TO THE CURRENT QUARTER OR A PREVIOUS QUARTER FOR RETROACTIVE ELIGIBILITY OR CORRECTION TO PREVIOUS INFORMATION.    REFERENCE TABLE: BENE_ELGBL_REC_TYPE_CD

name: BENE_EQTBL_BIC_CD
comment: A CODE IDENTIFYING AN EQUATABLE OR COMPARABLE BENEFICIARY IDENTIFICATION CODE (BIC) THAT REPRESENTS A SIMILAR RELATIONSHIP BETWEEN THE BENEFICIARY AND THE PRIMARY WAGE EARNER. BICS ARE EQUATABLE WHEN THEY IDENTIFY THE SAME PERSON (FOR EXAMPLE: WIFE/WIDOW).  REFERENCE TABLE: BENE_EQTBL_BIC_CD OR BENE_CTGRY_EQTBL_BIC_CD.

name: BENE_EQTBL_BIC_HICN_NUM
comment: A NUMBER COMPRISED OF THE BENEFICIARYS CLAIM ACCOUNT NUMBER (CAN) AND EQUATABLE BENEFICIARY IDENTIFICATION CODE (BIC) THAT IS LOGICALLY ASSOCIATED WITH A BENEFICIARY. FOR EXAMPLE  BICS B (WIFE) AND D (WIDOW) ARE EQUATABLE (THE WIFE/WIDOW IS ENTITLED TO MEDICARE BENEFITS UNDER HER HUSBANDÒ² SOCIAL SECURITY NUMBER). THE EQUATABLE HEALTH INSURANCE CLAIM NUMBERS (HICNS) WOULD THUS BE 999999999B AND 999999999D.

name: BENE_1ST_NAME
comment: A FIRST NAME FOR A MEDICARE BENEFICIARY.

name: BENE_LAST_NAME
comment: A LAST NAME OR SURNAME, INCLUDING ANY FOLLOWING TITLES OR SUFFIXES, FOR A MEDICARE BENEFICIARY.

name: BENE_HIC_NUM
comment: A MEDICARE HEALTH INSURANCE CLAIM NUMBER (HICN) CONSISTING OF A NINE DIGIT CLAIM ACCOUNT NUMBER (CAN) FOLLOWED BY A ONE OR TWO POSITION ALPHA-NUMERIC BENEFICIARY IDENTIFICATION CODE (BIC).  THIS COLUMN CONTAINS EITHER THE SOCIAL SECURITY ADMINISTRATION (SSA) HICN OR THE RAILROAD RETIREMENT BOARD (RRB) INTERNAL HICN.

name: BENE_MBI_ID
comment: AN IDENTIFIER THAT UNIQUELY IDENTIFIES A BENEFICIARY AND REPLACES THE HEALTH INSURANCE CLAIM NUMBER (HICN) ON MEDICARE CARDS. THE FORMAT OF THE MEDICARE BENEFICIARY IDENTIFIER (MBI) IS 11-POSITIONS IN LENGTH AND CONTAINS THE FOLLOWING VALUES:  POSITION 1 Ö NUMERIC VALUES: 1 - 9  POSITION 2 Ö ALPHABETIC VALUES: A - Z (MINUS S, L, O, I, B, Z)  POSITION 3 Ö ALPHANUMERIC VALUES: 0 - 9 AND A - Z (MINUS S, L, O, I, B, Z)  POSITION 4 Ö NUMERIC VALUES: 0 - 9  POSITION 5 Ö ALPHABETIC VALUES: A - Z (MINUS S, L, O, I, B, Z)  POSITION 6 Ö ALPHANUMERIC VALUES: 0 - 9 AND A - Z (MINUS S, L, O, I, B, Z)  POSITION 7 Ö NUMERIC VALUES: 0 - 9  POSITION 8 Ö ALPHABETIC VALUES: A - Z (MINUS S, L, O, I, B, Z)  POSITION 9 Ö ALPHABETIC VALUES: A - Z (MINUS S, L, O, I, B, Z)  POSITION 10 Ö NUMERIC VALUES: 0 - 9  POSITION 11 Ö NUMERIC VALUES: 0 - 9

name: BENE_MDCD_NUM
comment: A UNIQUE IDENTIFIER FOR A BENEFICIARY AS ASSIGNED BY A GIVEN STATE FOR MEDICAID COVERAGE.

name: BENE_MDCD_RCPNT_NUM
comment: A MEDICAID RECIPIENT IDENTIFICATION NUMBER ASSIGNED TO A BENEFICIARY.

name: BENE_MDCD_RCPNT_NUM_CHK_DGT
comment: A CHECK DIGIT ASSOCIATED WITH A BENEFICIARYS MEDICAID RECIPIENT IDENTIFICATION NUMBER.

name: BENE_MIDL_NAME
comment: THE FIRST INITIAL OF THE MEDICARE BENEFICIARYS MIDDLE NAME.

name: BENE_LINK_KEY
comment: AN UNIQUE NUMBER ASSIGNED BY THE ENROLLMENT DATABASE (EDB) TO EACH EDB BENEFICIARY RECORD.     NOTE: THIS COLUMN IS ONLY POPULATED WHEN THE INTEGRATED DATA REPOSITORY (IDR) RECEIVES A BENE_LINK_KEY FROM THE SOURCE SYSTEM.

name: BENE_PHNE_NUM
comment: A TELEPHONE NUMBER FOR A MEDICARE BENEFICIARY.

name: BENE_RACE_CD
comment: A CODE IDENTIFYING A BENEFICIARYS RACE.  REFERENCE TABLE: BENE_RACE_CD

name: BENE_RP_NAME
comment: A NAME FOR A PERSON OR ORGANIZATION THAT IS APPOINTED BY THE SOCIAL SECURITY ADMINISTRATION (SSA) TO RECEIVE PAYMENT FOR A QUALIFIED INDIVIDUALS BENEFIT BASED ON THE DETERMINATION OF THE SOCIAL SECURITY ADMINISTRATION THAT THE INTEREST OF THE QUALIFIED INDIVIDUAL WOULD BE SERVED.

name: BENE_RP_RSD_SW
comment: AN INDICATOR IDENTIFYING WHETHER THE BENEFICIARY LIVES WITH THE REPRESENTATIVE PAYEE.    REFERENCE TABLE: BENE_RP_RSD_SW

name: BENE_RP_SW
comment: AN INDICATOR IDENTIFYING WHETHER A BENEFICIARY HAS A REPRESENTATIVE PAYEE FOR SOCIAL SECURITY CASH BENEFIT PURPOSES.    REFERENCE TABLE: BENE_RP_SW

name: BENE_RRB_NUM
comment: A NUMBER IDENTIFYING A RAILROAD BOARD EMPLOYEE OR RETIRED RAILROAD BOARD MEDICARE BENEFICIARY. THIS NUMBER IS ALSO KNOWN AS THE RAILROAD RETIREMENT BOARD (RRB) EXTERNAL HEALTH INSURANCE CLAIM NUMBER (HICN). THE RAILROAD RETIREMENT BOARD IDENTIFIES ITS EMPLOYEES AND RETIREES WITH CLAIM NUMBERS THAT CONSIST OF LETTER PREFIXES FOLLOWED BY EITHER SIX OR NINE NUMERIC DIGITS.

name: BENE_RSDNC_MET_DT
comment: A DATE IDENTIFYING WHEN THE FIVE YEAR CONTINUOUS UNITED STATES RESIDENCY REQUIREMENT IS MET.  THIS DATE IS USED TO DERIVE THE INITIAL ENROLLMENT PERIOD FOR AN UNINSURED MEDICARE BENEFICIARY.

name: BENE_SEX_CD
comment: A CODE IDENTIFYING THE SEX OF A MEDICARE BENEFICIARY.     REFERENCE TABLE: BENE_SEX_CD

name: BENE_SSN_NUM
comment: A NUMBER IDENTIFYING A BENEFICIARY AS ASSIGNED BY THE SOCIAL SECURITY ADMINISTRATION (SSA).

name: BENE_VRFY_DEATH_DAY_SW
comment: AN INDICATION IF THE EXACT DATE OF DEATH FOR A MEDICARE BENEFICIARY WAS VERIFIED.  VALID VALUES:  Y = YES, DATE OF DEATH HAS BEEN VERIFIED.  N = NO, DATE OF DEATH HAS NOT BEEN VERIFIED.

name: CNTCT_LANG_CD
comment: A CODE IDENTIFYING THE LANGUAGE THAT THE BENEFICIARY REQUESTED CENTERS FOR MEDICARE AND MEDICAID SERVICES (CMS) USE WHEN SENDING THE MEDICARE HANDBOOK.  ENGLISH AND SPANISH ARE THE ONLY LANGUAGE CHOICES THAT CMS SUPPORTS.  THIS LANGUAGE PREFERENCE CODE IS USED EXCLUSIVELY FOR THE MEDICARE HANDBOOK.  IT IS NOT USED FOR ANY OTHER TYPE OF MAIL SENT TO BENEFICIARIES.    REFERENCE TABLE: CNTCT_LANG_CD

name: CNTCT_SRC_ID
comment: A UNIQUE IDENTIFIER OF A SOURCE THAT IS DERIVED BY THE INTEGRATED DATA REPOSITORY (IDR) AND POPULATED FOR DEFAULT RECORDS ONLY WITH A DEFAULT VALUE OF 10000.

name: CNTCT_LCL_LANG_CD
comment: A CODE IDENTIFYING THE LANGUAGE THAT THE BENEFICIARY REQUESTED CENTERS FOR MEDICARE AND MEDICAID SERVICES (CMS) USE WHEN SENDING THE MEDICARE HANDBOOK.  ENGLISH AND SPANISH ARE THE ONLY LANGUAGE CHOICES THAT CMS SUPPORTS.  THIS LANGUAGE PREFERENCE CODE IS USED EXCLUSIVELY FOR THE MEDICARE HANDBOOK.  IT IS NOT USED FOR ANY OTHER TYPE OF MAIL SENT TO BENEFICIARIES.    REFERENCE TABLE: CNTCT_LANG_CD

name: CNTCT_LANG_DLRY_TYPE_CD
comment: A CODE IDENTIFYING THE TYPE OF MEDIA THAT THE BENEFICIARY PREFERS CENTERS FOR MEDICARE AND MEDICAID SERVICES (CMS) USE WHEN SENDING THE MEDICARE HANDBOOK.    REFERENCE TABLE: CNTCT_LANG_DLRY_TYPE_CD

name: BENE_ADR_SQNC_NUM
comment: AN INTEGRATE DATA REPOSITORY (IDR) ASSIGNED NUMBER IDENTIFYING A VERSION OF A BENEFICIARY ADDRESS.

name: CNTCT_ADR_CONSLR_CD
comment: A CODE ASSIGNED TO THE AMERICAN CONSULATE IN A FOREIGN COUNTRY.  THIS CODE WILL IDENTIFY A FOREIGN ADDRESS IN THE MEDICARE BENEFICIARY DATABASE (MBD) FOR A BENEFICIARY.    REFERENCE TABLE: CNTCT_ADR_CONSLR_CD

name: CNTCT_ADR_SCRUB_CD
comment: AN INDICATOR OF WHETHER OR NOT THE BENEFICIARY ADDRESS RECORD WAS SUCCESSFULLY SCRUBBED (CLEANSED) BY THE FINALIST PROGRAM.     REFERENCE TABLE: CNTCT_ADR_SCRUB_CD

name: GEO_SK
comment: AN INTEGRATED DATA REPOSITORY (IDR) ASSIGNED NUMERIC SURROGATE KEY IDENTIFYING A PARTICULAR GEOGRAPHICAL LOCATION BY ITS FIVE-DIGIT ZIP CODE.

name: GEO_ZIP4_CD
comment: A FOUR-DIGIT ZIP CODE EXTENSION TO THE FIVE-DIGIT ZIP CODE DEFINED BY THE UNITED STATES POSTAL SERVICE (USPS) THAT REPRESENTS A SPECIFIC DELIVERY ROUTE WITHIN A DELIVERY AREA.    REFERENCE TABLE: GEO_ZIP9_CD

name: BENE_ADR_BGN_DT
comment: A DATE IDENTIFYING THE EFFECTIVE DATE FOR THIS VERSION OF THE BENEFICIARYS ADDRESS.

name: BENE_LINE_1_ADR
comment: A FIRST LINE OF A BENEFICIARY STREET ADDRESS.

name: BENE_LINE_2_ADR
comment: A SECOND LINE OF A BENEFICIARY STREET ADDRESS.

name: BENE_LINE_3_ADR
comment: A THIRD LINE OF A BENEFICIARY STREET ADDRESS.

name: BENE_LINE_4_ADR
comment: A FOURTH LINE OF A BENEFICIARY MAILING ADDRESS.

name: BENE_LINE_5_ADR
comment: A FIFTH LINE OF A BENEFICIARY MAILING ADDRESS.

name: BENE_LINE_6_ADR
comment: A SIXTH LINE OF A BENEFICIARY MAILING ADDRESS.

name: GEO_ZIP5_CD
comment: A FIVE-DIGIT ZIP CODE DEFINED BY THE UNITED STATES POSTAL SERVICE (USPS) THAT IDENTIFIES THE DESTINATION POST OFFICE OR DELIVERY AREA.     REFERENCE TABLE: GEO_ZIP5_CD

name: GEO_USPS_STATE_CD
comment: A CODE IDENTIFYING THE TWO-CHARACTER ALPHABETIC ABBREVIATION FOR A STATE IN THE UNITED STATES AS DEFINED BY THE UNITED STATES POSTAL SERVICE (USPS).    REFERENCE TABLE: GEO_USPS_STATE_CD

name: GEO_ZIP_PLC_NAME
comment: A NAME OF THE CITY FOR A GIVEN ZIP CODE OF A MEDICARE BENEFICIARYS MAILING ADDRESS.    REFERENCE TABLE: GEO_ZIP5_CD

name: META_SSN_SK
comment: A UNIQUE LEGACY NUMERIC VALUE ASSIGNED BY THE INTEGRATED DATA REPOSITORY (IDR), FORMULATED WITH A DATE AND A 3-DIGIT SEQUENCE NUMBER, WHICH IDENTIFIES THE BATCH PROCESS THAT INITIALLY LOADED A ROW IN THE IDR BASED ON CME_SSN SOURCE DATA. DUE TO THE LIMITATION OF A 3-DIGIT VALUE, THIS IS BEING REPLACED BY META_SRC_PRCSG_ID ON NEW IDR TABLES AS THE SOURCE DATA TRACKING STANDARD.

name: META_NAME_SK
comment: A UNIQUE LEGACY NUMERIC VALUE ASSIGNED BY THE INTEGRATED DATA REPOSITORY (IDR), FORMULATED WITH A DATE AND A 3-DIGIT SEQUENCE NUMBER, WHICH IDENTIFIES THE BATCH PROCESS THAT INITIALLY LOADED A ROW IN THE IDR BASED ON CME_BENE_NAME SOURCE DATA. DUE TO THE LIMITATION OF A 3-DIGIT VALUE, THIS IS BEING REPLACED BY META_SRC_PRCSG_ID ON NEW IDR TABLES AS THE SOURCE DATA TRACKING STANDARD.

name: META_ADR_SK
comment: A UNIQUE LEGACY NUMERIC VALUE ASSIGNED BY THE INTEGRATED DATA REPOSITORY (IDR), FORMULATED WITH A DATE AND A 3-DIGIT SEQUENCE NUMBER, WHICH IDENTIFIES THE BATCH PROCESS THAT INITIALLY LOADED A ROW IN THE IDR BASED ON CME_DRVD_MLG_ADR SOURCE DATA. DUE TO THE LIMITATION OF A 3-DIGIT VALUE, THIS IS BEING REPLACED BY META_SRC_PRCSG_ID ON NEW IDR TABLES AS THE SOURCE DATA TRACKING STANDARD.

name: META_SSN_LAST_UPDT_SK
comment: A UNIQUE LEGACY NUMERIC VALUE ASSIGNED BY THE INTEGRATED DATA REPOSITORY (IDR), FORMULATED WITH A DATE AND A 3-DIGIT SEQUENCE NUMBER, WHICH IDENTIFIES THE BATCH PROCESS THAT INITIALLY LOADED A ROW IN THE IDR BASED ON CME_SSN SOURCE DATA. DUE TO THE LIMITATION OF A 3-DIGIT VALUE, THIS IS BEING REPLACED BY META_SRC_PRCSG_ID ON NEW IDR TABLES AS THE SOURCE DATA TRACKING STANDARD.

name: META_NAME_LAST_UPDT_SK
comment: A UNIQUE LEGACY NUMERIC VALUE ASSIGNED BY THE INTEGRATED DATA REPOSITORY (IDR), FORMULATED WITH A DATE AND A 3-DIGIT SEQUENCE NUMBER, WHICH IDENTIFIES THE BATCH PROCESS THAT INITIALLY LOADED A ROW IN THE IDR BASED ON CME_BENE_NAME SOURCE DATA. DUE TO THE LIMITATION OF A 3-DIGIT VALUE, THIS IS BEING REPLACED BY META_SRC_PRCSG_ID ON NEW IDR TABLES AS THE SOURCE DATA TRACKING STANDARD.

name: META_ADR_LAST_UPDT_SK
comment: A UNIQUE LEGACY NUMERIC VALUE ASSIGNED BY THE INTEGRATED DATA REPOSITORY (IDR), FORMULATED WITH A DATE AND A 3-DIGIT SEQUENCE NUMBER, WHICH IDENTIFIES THE BATCH PROCESS THAT INITIALLY LOADED A ROW IN THE IDR BASED ON CME_DRVD_MLG_ADR SOURCE DATA. DUE TO THE LIMITATION OF A 3-DIGIT VALUE, THIS IS BEING REPLACED BY META_SRC_PRCSG_ID ON NEW IDR TABLES AS THE SOURCE DATA TRACKING STANDARD.

name: BENE_ACRTN_DT
comment: A DATE WHEN A BENEFICIARY RECORD WAS INITIALLY ESTABLISHED ON THE ENROLLMENT DATA BASE (EDB). ALL RECORDS THAT WERE ALREADY ON THE EDB AS OF 11/22/91 WERE ARBITRARILY ASSIGNED AN ACCRETION DATE OF 11/22/91.

name: BENE_INCRCRTN_EXCPTN_SW
comment: A SWITCH INDICATING WHETHER A BENEFICIARY MAY HAVE BEEN INCARCERATED. THIS COLUMN IS POPULATED WITH Y WHEN THE BENEFICIARY EXISTS ON BENE_INCRCRTN, WHICH CAPTURES PERIODS WHERE A BENEFICIARY IS CONFINED TO A PENAL INSTITUTION.  VALID VALUES:  Y = BENEFICIARY HAS INCARCERATION PERIODS  N = BENEFICIARY DOES NOT HAVE INCARCERATION PERIODS  U = UNKNOWN    REFERENCE TABLE: BENE_INCRCRTN_EXCPTN_SW

name: BENE_PSC_CD
comment: A CODE IDENTIFYING THE SOCIAL SECURITY ADMINISTRATION (SSA) PROGRAM SERVICE CENTER (PSC) THAT IS RETAINING THE BENEFICIARYS FOLDER. THE ELEMENT WILL BE USEFUL IF A CUSTOMER SERVICE REPRESENTATIVE MUST CONTACT A PSC FOR PROBLEM CASE RESOLUTION.    REFERENCE TABLE: BENE_PSC_CD

name: BENE_CLRCL_NAME_CHG_SW
comment: A SWITCH THAT PROTECTS A CLERICALLY CORRECTED BENEFICIARY NAME FROM BEING CHANGED BY AN SOCIAL SECURITY ADMINISTRATION/ RAILROAD RETIREMENT BOARD (SSA/RRB) UPDATE TRANSACTION.  WHEN THE SSA/RRB UPDATE CONTAINS A NAME THAT MATCHES THE GIVEN NAME, MIDDLE INITIAL AND SURNAME ON THE COMMON MEDICARE ENVIRONMENT (CME) DATABASE, THE CLERICAL NAME CHANGE SWITCH IS TURNED OFF.  VALID VALUES:  1 = CLERICAL NAME CHANGE PROCESSED: PROTECT THE CME NAME FROM BEING CHANGED BY AN UPDATE TRANSACTION  ~ OR BLANK = NAME IS NOT PROTECTED FROM CHANGE

name: BENE_CLRCL_SEX_CD_CRCTN_SW
comment: A SWITCH THAT PROTECTS A CLERICALLY CORRECTED SEX CODE FROM BEING CHANGED BY AN SOCIAL SECURITY ADMINISTRATION/ RAILROAD RETIREMENT BOARD (SSA/RRB) UPDATE TRANSACTION.  WHEN THE SSA/RRB UPDATE TRANSACTION CONTAINS A SEX CODE THAT MATCHES THE SEX CODE ON THE COMMON MEDICARE ENVIRONMENT (CME) DATABASE, THE CLERICAL SEX CORRECTION SWITCH IS TURNED OFF.  VALID VALUES:  1 = CLERICAL SEX CODE PROCESSED: PROTECT THE CME SEX CODE FROM BEING CHANGED BY AN UPDATE TRANSACTION  ~ OR BLANK = NO CLERICAL CORRECTION APPLIED

name: BENE_CMBND_US_FRGN_ERNG_SW
comment: AN INDICATOR IDENTIFYING WHETHER A MEDICARE BENEFICIARYS EARNINGS FROM A FOREIGN COUNTRY, WITH WHICH THE UNITED STATES HAS AN AGREEMENT, HAVE BEEN COMBINED WITH EARNINGS FROM THE UNITED STATES TO ESTABLISH ELIGIBILITY FOR BENEFITS.  THIS COMBINATION IS NEEDED TO ACCOMMODATE THE ASSESSMENT/TOTALIZATION OF BENEFITS LEGISLATION.   ALTHOUGH THESE INDIVIDUALS HAVE AN INSURED BENEFICIARY IDENTIFICATION CODE (BIC) BECAUSE THEY ARE INSURED FOR A SOCIAL SECURITY ADMINISTRATION (SSA) CASH BENEFIT, THEY MAY HAVE NO PART A COVERAGE OR PREMIUM BASED PART A COVERAGE.  VALID VALUES:  Y = YES, FOREIGN COUNTRY EARNINGS ARE INCLUDED.  N = NO, FOREIGN COUNTRY EARNING ARE NOT INCLUDED.

name: BENE_DB_PTA_OPEN_SW
comment: AN INDICATOR IDENTIFYING WHETHER A BENEFICIARY HAS A CURRENT OPEN PART A DIRECT BILL PERIOD.  VALID VALUES:   Y = BENEFICIARY HAS AN OPEN PART A DIRECT BILL PERIOD.  N = BENEFICIARY DOES NOT HAVE AN OPEN PART A DIRECT BILL PERIOD.  ~ OR BLANK = DEFAULT.

name: BENE_DB_PTB_OPEN_SW
comment: AN INDICATOR IDENTIFYING WHETHER A BENEFICIARY HAS A CURRENT OPEN PART B DIRECT BILL PERIOD.  VALID VALUES:   Y = BENEFICIARY HAS AN OPEN PART B DIRECT BILL PERIOD.  N = BENEFICIARY DOES NOT HAVE AN OPEN PART B DIRECT BILL PERIOD.  ~ OR BLANK = DEFAULT.

name: BENE_DB_PTD_IRMAA_OPEN_SW
comment: AN INDICATOR IDENTIFYING A BENEFICIARYS PART D INCOME-RELATED MONTHLY ADJUSTMENT AMOUNT (IRMAA)  STATUS.  VALID VALUES:  Y = BENEFICIARY IS CURRENTLY DIRECT BILLED FOR THEIR PART D IRMAA PREMIUM.  N = BENEFICIARY WAS PREVIOUSLY DIRECT BILLED FOR THEIR PART D IRMAA PREMIUM.  NULL = BENEFICIARY HAS NEVER BEEN INVOLVED IN DIRECT BILLING FOR PART D IRMAA

name: BENE_DSCRPNT_NAME_SW
comment: AN INDICATION THAT THE SOCIAL SECURITY ADMINISTRATION (SSA) COMBINED EXCHANGE RECORD (CER) TRANSACTIONS GIVEN NAME OR SURNAME FIELD DISAGREES WITH THE NAME HOUSED IN THE CERS PAYMENT NAME/ADDRESS LINES.  VALID VALUES:  1 = DISCREPANT BENEFICIARY NAME. THE SOCIAL SECURITY ADMINISTRATION (SSA) TRANSACTIONS NAME LEGEND IS DIFFERENT THAN THE NAME IN THE ADDRESS LEGEND.  ~ OR BLANK = BENEFICIARYS NAME IS NOT DISCREPANT

name: BENE_DSTR_CD
comment: A CODE IDENTIFYING THE SPECIFIC DISASTER AFFECTING THE BENEFICIARY.

name: BENE_REC_CMPLTNS_CD
comment: A CODE IDENTIFYING WHETHER A BENEFICIARY RECORD CONTAINS FULL INFORMATION OR ONLY SKELETON DATA IN THE ENROLLMENT DATABASE (EDB).  ACTIVE BENEFICIARY RECORDS CONTAIN FULL INFORMATION.  SKELETON RECORDS EXIST FOR CERTAIN DECEASED INDIVIDUALS WHO WERE PURGED FROM THE ACTIVE AND INACTIVE ENROLLMENT MASTER FILES PRIOR TO 1978.  SKELETON RECORDS INCLUDE ONLY NAME, DATE OF BIRTH, DATE OF DEATH, SEX CODE, RACE CODE AND SOME RESIDENCE DATA. ON THE UNLOADED, SEQUENTIAL EDB FILE, THIS CODE IS USED TO IDENTIFY EACH OCCURRENCE OF THE VARIOUS EDB RELATIONS.  VALID VALUES:  A = ACTIVE RECORD  B = SKELETON RECORD  NULL = DEFAULT

name: BENE_ENRLMT_DLT_SW
comment: AN INDICATION IF A BENEFICIARY ENROLLMENT RECORD IS OR HAS EVER BEEN ON THE ENROLLMENT DATABASE (EDB) INACTIVE MASTER FILE.  VALID VALUES:  N = ENROLLMENT RECORD NOT DELETED.  Y AND BENE_REC_CMPLTNS_CD = B (INACTIVE EDB RECORD):  THE PRE-1976 BENEFICIARY RECORD WAS PURGED FROM THE INACTIVE MASTER FILE.    Y AND BENE_REC_CMPLTNS_CD = A (ACTIVE EDB RECORD):  THIS RECORD WAS PREVIOUSLY ON THE INACTIVE FILE AND WAS SUCCESSFULLY RE-ACTIVATED.

name: BENE_GNRL_ENRLMT_SOLCTNCD
comment: A CODE INDICATING WHETHER THE CENTERS FOR MEDICARE AND MEDICAID SERVICES (CMS) SOLICITED A BENEFICIARY DURING A MEDICARE PART B GENERAL ENROLLMENT PERIOD (GEP). THIS IS FOR INDIVIDUALS WHO IN THE PRIOR YEAR REFUSED PART B COVERAGE, WITHDREW FROM PART B COVERAGE, OR TERMINATED FROM PART B COVERAGE BASED ON NONPAYMENT OF PREMIUMS.    VALID VALUES:  ~ OR BLANK = NOT SELECTED FOR GEP SOLICITATION  S = SELECTED FOR GEP SOLICITATION  Y = RESPONDED YES TO GEP SOLICITATION

name: BENE_MDCR_CARD_RQST_DT
comment: A DATE IDENTIFYING WHEN A CLERICAL REQUEST WAS MADE FOR A MEDICARE HEALTH INSURANCE (HI) CARD OR CHANGES IN ENTITLEMENT REQUIRED THAT A NEW CARD BE ISSUED.

name: BENE_MDCR_CARD_TYPE_CD
comment: A CODE INDICATING THE TYPE OF MEDICARE CARD TO BE PRODUCED FOR A BENEFICIARY.  VALID VALUES:  R = PART A ENTITLEMENT HAS TERMINATED, BUT PART B ENTITLEMENT REMAINS OPEN.  S = PART B ENTITLEMENT HAS TERMINATED, BUT PART A ENTITLEMENT REMAINS OPEN.  V = FOREIGN OR PUERTO RICAN ENROLLMENT.  DEFAULT IS NULL.

name: BENE_PTA_NENTLMT_RSN_CD
comment: A CODE IDENTIFYING THE REASON FOR A BENEFICIARYS CURRENT NON-ENTITLEMENT TO PART A MEDICARE BENEFITS.    REFERENCE TABLE: BENE_PTA_NENTLMT_RSN_CD

name: BENE_PTA_TP_PRM_PYR_CD
comment: A CODE INDICATING THE TYPE OF THIRD PARTY THAT PAID THE MEDICARE BENEFICIARYS PART A OR PART B PREMIUMS.    WHEN STATE BILLING IS INVOLVED, THE CODE INDICATES THAT THE BENEFICIARY IS DUALLY ELIGIBLE FOR MEDICARE AND MEDICAID.  THIS CODE IDENTIFIES MOST, BUT NOT ALL, PART A AND PART B DUAL ELIGIBLE BENEFICIARIES.    IF A STATE DOES NOT PAY PREMIUMS FOR CERTAIN ELIGIBILITY GROUPS (MEDICAL ASSISTANCE ONLY GROUPS, FOR EXAMPLE), THIS CODE WOULD NOT REFLECT A DUAL ELIGIBLE STATUS.

name: BENE_PTB_NENTLMT_RSN_CD
comment: THE REASON FOR A BENEFICIARYS CURRENT NON-ENTITLEMENT TO PART A MEDICARE BENEFITS.    D	COVERAGE WAS DENIED   F	TERMINATED DUE TO INVALID ENROLLMENT                  OR ENROLLMENT VOIDED   H	NOT ELIGIBLE FOR FREE PART A, OR DID NOT                 ENROL

name: BENE_PTB_TP_PRM_PYR_CD
comment: A CODE INDICATING THE TYPE OF THIRD PARTY THAT PAID THE MEDICARE BENEFICIARYS PART A OR PART B PREMIUMS.    WHEN STATE BILLING IS INVOLVED, THE CODE INDICATES THAT THE BENEFICIARY IS DUALLY ELIGIBLE FOR MEDICARE AND MEDICAID.  THIS CODE IDENTIFIES MOST, BUT NOT ALL, PART A AND PART B DUAL ELIGIBLE BENEFICIARIES.    IF A STATE DOES NOT PAY PREMIUMS FOR CERTAIN ELIGIBILITY GROUPS (MEDICAL ASSISTANCE ONLY GROUPS, FOR EXAMPLE), THIS CODE WOULD NOT REFLECT A DUAL ELIGIBLE STATUS.

name: BENE_RACE_SRC_CD
comment: A CODE IDENTIFYING THE SOURCE OF A BENEFICIARYS ENROLLMENT DATABASE (EDB) RACE CODE.  VALID VALUES:  A = RESPONSE FROM A ONE-TIME SURVEY THAT WAS MAILED TO CERTAIN BENEFICIARIES IN 1995.  B = INDIAN HEALTH SERVICE  ~ OR BLANK = SOCIAL SECURITY ADMINISTRATION (SSA) MASTER BENEFICIARY RECORD (MBR) FILE, SOCIAL SECURITY ADMINISTRATION (SSA) NUMIDENT FILE OR RAILROAD RETIREMENT BOARD (RRB) RECORD.

name: BENE_SSA_LANG_CD
comment: A CODE IDENTIFYING THE LANGUAGE A BENEFICIARY HAS REQUESTED SOCIAL SECURITY ADMINISTRATION (SSA) TO USE FOR BENEFICIARY NOTICES. CENTERS FOR MEDICARE AND MEDICAID SERVICES (CMS) USES THIS CODE WHEN MAILING MEDICARE PREMIUM BILLS (DIRECT BILLING).  VALID VALUES:  ~ OR BLANK = ENGLISH ASSUMED FOR NON-PUERTO RICAN ZIP CODES; SPANISH ASSUMED FOR PUERTO RICAN ZIP CODES  E =  ENGLISH REQUESTED FOR PUERTO RICAN ZIP CODES  S = SPANISH REQUESTED

name: BENE_SSN_VRFY_SW
comment: AN INDICATOR IDENTIFYING WHETHER THE SOCIAL SECURITY ADMINISTRATION (SSA) HAS VERIFIED THE BENEFICIARYS CURRENT SOCIAL SECURITY NUMBER (SSN).  VALID VALUES:  Y = CURRENT SSN HAS BEEN VERIFIED  N = CURRENT SSN HAS NOT BEEN VERIFIED  ~ OR BLANK = NOT APPLICABLE

name: BENE_XREF_SK
comment: AN INTEGRATED DATA REPOSITORY (IDR) DERIVED SURROGATE KEY THAT UNIQUELY IDENTIFIES A BENEFICIARY.  ON THE BENE TABLE, THE BENE_XREF_SK REPRESENTS BENE_SKS FORWARDING BENE_SK.   IF BENE_XREF_SK AND BENE_SK ARE NOT IDENTICAL, THEN BENE_SK WAS

name: META_SK
comment: A UNIQUE LEGACY NUMERIC VALUE ASSIGNED BY THE INTEGRATED DATA REPOSITORY (IDR), FORMULATED WITH A DATE AND A 3-DIGIT SEQUENCE NUMBER, WHICH IDENTIFIES THE BATCH PROCESS THAT INITIALLY LOADED A ROW IN THE IDR. DUE TO THE LIMITATION OF A 3-DIGIT VALUE, THIS IS BEING REPLACED BY META_SRC_PRCSG_ID ON NEW IDR TABLES AS THE SOURCE DATA TRACKING STANDARD.

name: META_LST_UPDT_SK
comment: A UNIQUE LEGACY NUMERIC VALUE ASSIGNED BY THE INTEGRATED DATA REPOSITORY (IDR), FORMULATED WITH A DATE AND 3-DIGIT SEQUENCE NUMBER, WHICH IDENTIFIES THE BATCH PROCESS THAT UPDATED A ROW IN THE IDR. DUE TO THE LIMITATION OF A 3-DIGIT VALUE, THIS IS BEING REPLACED BY META_LTST_SRC_PRCSG_ID ON NEW IDR TABLES AS THE SOURCE DATA TRACKING STANDARD.

name: META_SRC_SK
comment: A UNIQUE NUMERIC VALUE ASSIGNED BY THE INTEGRATED DATA REPOSITORY (IDR) USED TO IDENTIFY THE SPECIFIC SOURCE OF THE DATA WHEN A ROW IS LOADED INTO THE IDR.    REFERENCE TABLE: V2_MDCR_META_DCTNRY_SRC

name: META_LST_UPDT_SRC_SK
comment: A UNIQUE NUMERIC VALUE ASSIGNED BY THE INTEGRATED DATA REPOSITORY (IDR) USED TO IDENTIFY THE SPECIFIC SOURCE OF THE DATA WHEN A ROW IS UPDATED IN THE IDR.

name: IDR_INSRT_TS
comment: THE SYSTEM DATE AND TIME ASSIGNED BY THE INTEGRATED DATA REPOSITORY (IDR) WHILE PERFORMING AN INSERT OPERATION.

name: IDR_UPDT_TS
comment: THE SYSTEM DATE AND TIME ASSIGNED BY THE INTEGRATED DATA REPOSITORY (IDR) WHEN UPDATES ARE MADE TO ANY NON-PRIMARY KEY COLUMN.

name: BENE_DISP_CD
comment: A CODE IDENTIFYING THE STATUS OF A BENEFICIARY SURROGATEKEY (BENE_SK) IN THE COMMON MEDICARE ENVIRONMENT (CME).    REFERENCE TABLE: BENE_DISP_CD

name: BENE_LAT_QTY
comment: A NUMBER IDENTIFYING THE DISTANCE (IN DEGREES) NORTH OR SOUTH OF THE EQUATOR, KNOWN AS LATITUDE.      A LATITUDE NORTH OF THE EQUATOR IS SPECIFIED BY A PLUS SIGN (+), OR BY THE ABSENCE OF A MINUS SIGN (-), AND A LATITUDE SOUTH OF THE EQUATOR IS SPECIFIED BY A MINUS SIGN (-), PRECEDING THE TWO DIGITS DESIGNATING DEGREES OF LATITUDE.     FOR EXAMPLE: -12.046374 = LIMA, PERU (SOUTH OF THE EQUATOR) 43.653908 = TORONTO, CANADA (NORTH OF THE EQUATOR)     A LATITUDE COORDINATE IS THE SECOND OF AN ORDERED PAIR OF NUMBERS USED TO LOCATE A SPECIFIC PLACE ON THE EARTH.

name: BENE_LON_QTY
comment: A NUMBER IDENTIFYING THE DISTANCE (IN DEGREES) EAST OR WEST OF THE PRIME MERIDIAN, KNOWN AS LONGITUDE.      A LONGITUDE EAST OF THE PRIME MERIDIAN IS SPECIFIED BY A PLUS SIGN (+), OR BY THE ABSENCE OF A MINUS SIGN (-), AND A LONGITUDE WEST OF THE PRIME MERIDIAN IS SPECIFIED BY A MINUS SIGN (-), PRECEDING THE THREE DIGITS DESIGNATING DEGREES OF LONGITUDE.     FOR EXAMPLE: -104.991531 = DENVER, CO (WEST OF THE PRIME MERIDIAN) 114.15769 = HONG KONG (EAST OF THE PRIME MERIDIAN)     A LONGITUDE COORDINATE IS THE FIRST OF AN ORDERED PAIR OF NUMBERS USED TO LOCATE A SPECIFIC PLACE ON THE EARTH.

name: BENE_CNSUS_TRCT_NUM
comment: A NUMBER SIGNIFYING AN AREA ROUGHLY EQUIVALENT TO A NEIGHBORHOOD ESTABLISHED BY THE UNITED STATES BUREAU OF CENSUS FOR ANALYZING POPULATION.    MAY BE REFERRED TO AS CENSUS TRACT, CENSUS AREA, CENSUS DISTRICT OR CENSUS MESHBLOCK FOR THE PURPOSE OF TAKING A CENSUS.

name: BENE_CNSUS_BLK_NUM
comment: A NUMBER SIGNIFYING THE SMALLEST GEOGRAPHIC UNIT USED BY THE UNITED STATES CENSUS BUREAU FOR TABULATION OF 100-PERCENT DATA (I.E. DATA COLLECTED FROM ALL HOUSES VERSUS A SAMPLING OF HOUSES).

name: IDR_LTST_TRANS_FLG
comment: AN INDICATOR ASSIGNED BY THE INTEGRATED DATA REPOSITORY (IDR) THAT IDENTIFIES WHICH TRANSACTION RECORD, BASED ON PRIMARY KEY, IS CONSIDERED TO REPRESENT THE MOST RECENT RECORD RECEIVED FROM THE SOURCE.    Y = LATEST VERSION OF THE RECORD  N = PREVIOUS VERSION OF THE RECORD
